PROJECT OVERVIEW
================================================================================

NeuroAssist is a comprehensive web-based cognitive health monitoring platform 
designed for early detection of dementia and continuous tracking of cognitive 
function. The system provides accessible tools for patients to log daily 
activities, complete cognitive assessments, and practice brain exercises, while 
enabling caregivers to monitor cognitive health trends and receive real-time 
alerts about concerning patterns.

This is a clinically-informed, browser-based solution that requires NO external 
devices, cameras, sensors, or machine learning models, making it immediately 
deployable and highly accessible.


PURPOSE & OBJECTIVES
================================================================================

Primary Purpose:
    Enable early detection of cognitive decline through passive monitoring and 
    structured assessments, providing caregivers with actionable insights while 
    maintaining patient dignity and independence.

Key Objectives:
    1. ACCESSIBILITY: Provide large, clear interfaces suitable for elderly users
    2. EARLY DETECTION: Identify cognitive decline patterns before clinical symptoms
    3. CONTINUOUS MONITORING: Track daily routines, mood, and cognitive performance
    4. CAREGIVER SUPPORT: Deliver real-time alerts and trend analysis
    5. NON-INVASIVE: Require no special equipment or technical expertise
    6. CLINICAL VALIDITY: Use evidence-based cognitive assessment methods


WHAT IT DOES
================================================================================

Patient-Facing Features:

    ✓ DAILY ROUTINE TRACKER
        - One-click logging for medications, meals, water intake, sleep
        - Mood tracking with visual emoji-based selection
        - Timestamp-based activity recording
        - Encouraging feedback and positive reinforcement

    ✓ COGNITIVE ASSESSMENTS
        - Orientation Test: Date, day of week, current location (MMSE-based)
        - Five-Word Recall Test: Immediate and delayed memory assessment
        - Trail-Making Test: Number sequencing for executive function testing
        - Automated scoring with clinical interpretation

    ✓ BRAIN EXERCISE GAMES
        - Matching Pairs: Memory game with time and error tracking
        - Progressive difficulty levels
        - Performance analytics stored for trend analysis

    ✓ FUNCTIONAL TASK SIMULATION
        - "Make a Cup of Tea" step-by-step workflow
        - Sequence validation and error detection
        - Cognitive challenge variations (e.g., ingredient selection)
        - Completion time tracking

    ✓ BASELINE ASSESSMENT (Onboarding)
        - Comprehensive initial cognitive evaluation
        - Establishes personal baseline for future comparison
        - Risk level classification: Normal / Mild / High
        - Generates personalized monitoring recommendations

Caregiver-Facing Features:

    ✓ REAL-TIME DASHBOARD
        - Consolidated view of all patient activities
        - Color-coded risk score (0-10 scale with traffic-light status)
        - Today's activities summary
        - Unread alerts counter

    ✓ COGNITIVE STABILITY GRAPH
        - 7-day trend visualization showing risk score over time
        - Visual pattern recognition for decline detection
        - Automatic baseline comparison

    ✓ ALERT SYSTEM
        - Rule-driven notifications for:
            * Missed medications
            * Low cognitive test scores
            * Abnormal functional task performance
            * Negative mood patterns
            * Significant decline vs. baseline
        - Priority levels: High, Medium, Low
        - Read/unread status tracking

    ✓ PERFORMANCE ANALYTICS
        - Cognitive test performance comparison
        - Routine adherence heatmap (7-day view)
        - Functional task success rates
        - Trend analysis reports


HOW IT'S BUILT
================================================================================

Architecture Overview:
    Three-tier web application with RESTful API, persistent data storage, and 
    modern responsive frontend.

Technology Stack:

    BACKEND:
        • Node.js v14+ (JavaScript runtime)
        • Express.js 4.18+ (Web framework)
        • Better-SQLite3 12.5+ (Embedded database)
        • UUID v9 (Unique identifier generation)
        • CORS & Body-Parser (Middleware)

    FRONTEND:
        • Vanilla HTML5 (Semantic markup)
        • CSS3 with Custom Properties (Design system)
        • Vanilla JavaScript ES6+ (No frameworks)
        • Canvas API (Custom chart rendering)

    DATABASE:
        • SQLite (Persistent relational database)
        • Schema: 7 tables with foreign key relationships
        • Indexed queries for performance
        • JSON storage for complex data structures

    DEPLOYMENT:
        • Single-server architecture
        • Static file serving via Express
        • Port 3000 (configurable via environment variable)

Database Schema:

    users:
        - Stores patient and caregiver accounts
        - Fields: id, name, role, date_of_birth, caregiver_id, onboarding_completed

    baseline_assessments:
        - Initial cognitive evaluation results
        - Fields: cognitive_score, functional_score, total_score, risk_level, components

    routine_logs:
        - Daily activity tracking (medication, meals, mood, etc.)
        - Fields: activity, value, mood, timestamp

    cognitive_tests:
        - Test results from orientation, recall, trail-making assessments
        - Fields: test_type, score, max_score, time_taken, details

    functional_tasks:
        - Tea-making and similar task performance
        - Fields: task_type, completed, errors, sequence_correct, time_taken, steps

    alerts:
        - System-generated notifications for caregivers
        - Fields: type, priority, message, data, read, timestamp

    risk_scores:
        - Historical risk score calculations
        - Fields: score, status, breakdown, timestamp

API Endpoints (RESTful):

    USER MANAGEMENT:
        POST   /api/users          - Create new user
        POST   /api/login          - User authentication
        GET    /api/users/:userId  - Get user details

    BASELINE ASSESSMENT:
        POST   /api/baseline-assessment           - Submit onboarding results
        GET    /api/baseline-assessment/:userId   - Get baseline data
        GET    /api/baseline-report/:userId       - Get report with recommendations

    ROUTINE LOGGING:
        POST   /api/routine-log        - Log daily activity
        GET    /api/routine-log/:userId?days=7   - Get routine history

    COGNITIVE TESTS:
        POST   /api/cognitive-test       - Submit test results
        GET    /api/cognitive-test/:userId?days=7  - Get test history

    FUNCTIONAL TASKS:
        POST   /api/functional-task       - Submit task completion
        GET    /api/functional-task/:userId?days=7  - Get task history

    ANALYTICS & ALERTS:
        GET    /api/dashboard/:userId     - Get all dashboard data
        GET    /api/risk-score/:userId    - Calculate current risk score
        GET    /api/trend-analysis/:userId - Compare current vs baseline
        GET    /api/alerts/:userId        - Get alerts
        PATCH  /api/alerts/:alertId/read  - Mark alert as read

Risk Scoring Algorithm:

    Base Score: 10 (perfect health)
    
    Deductions:
        - Missed medications (7 days):  -1 per missed dose
        - Abnormal functional tasks:    -2 per failed task
        - Low memory recall (<60%):     -1 point
        - Slow trail-making (<50%):     -1 point
        - Negative mood days:           -1 per day
        - Cognitive decline (>10% vs baseline): -1 to -2 points
    
    Final Score: Clamped to 0-10 range
    
    Status Classification:
        • 8-10 = GREEN (Good condition)
        • 5-7  = AMBER (Needs attention)
        • 0-4  = RED (Immediate concern)

