CLINICAL BASIS
================================================================================

The cognitive tests implemented are based on validated clinical assessments:

    ORIENTATION TEST:
        - Based on Mini-Mental State Examination (MMSE)
        - Tests temporal and spatial orientation
        - 3 questions: current date, day of week, location
        - Scoring: 1 point per correct answer (max 3)

    FIVE-WORD RECALL:
        - Based on Montreal Cognitive Assessment (MoCA)
        - Tests immediate and delayed memory
        - 5 common words presented, then recalled after distraction
        - Scoring: 1 point per correct word (max 5)

    TRAIL-MAKING TEST (Simplified):
        - Based on Trail Making Test Part A
        - Tests visual attention and executive function
        - Number sequencing task (1-10)
        - Scoring: Based on time and errors

    FUNCTIONAL TASK ASSESSMENT:
        - Based on Activities of Daily Living (ADL) evaluation
        - Simulates real-world task completion
        - Tracks sequence accuracy and error patterns


